to be perfectly honest, my problem started at 51, when i started looking at my 50-59 spells... all of them were less damage than a 49 spell... ive been moderately disappointed since then. <br>
<br>
i know a lot of you may say BLA BLA they are more efficient, but i will tell you one thing, it SURE took a lot of the fun out of it. IMO wizards have been castrated. we were made for burst damage, the game changed literally at that point. i became reliant on quadding for xp... and a lot of people may argue, but group desirability for wizards is pathetically low, and it's NOT just perception. the class is underpowered groupwise, decent soloers, and good clean DPS for raids.<br>
<br>
instead of the spells scaling normally after 49, they actually decrease damage until 60.. where you get ice spear and sunstrike(if you are rich or lucky). Throughout these 10 levels.. you only get a small damage increase per nuke for the excuse of increased efficiency. this is not viable. why? it changes our role in a group.. from the guy who can get rid of that last 20% with a couple of nukes so u don't have to worry about it running, to just another damage dealer. a damage dealer who can't tank.. who can't buff.  a wizard's nuke should NOT take less than a tenth of a mobs HP.. its SUPPOSED to be a NUKE, not a magic missile.. a lightning bolt, not a backstab.. it should be a SUNSTRIKE not a slap on the wrist. from a roleplay perspective this completely ruins being a wizard for me. Mages can nuke just as hard.. AND they have a pet. YES they are less efficient and they run out of mana quick.. but that doesnt mean they cant crit for 5k just like a wizard can. on top of that, they can summon lots of neato stuff. Both mages and rogues in most situations have higher DPS.. a wizard is completely and utterly dependent on his mana pool, and everything a wizard does besides nukes,evacs, and TLs is utterly useless.. the damage shields? alkabor line? wait, how about i levitate you!! (nm im out of batwings) any buffs that you can buff yourself with someone else can give you better.. any damage we deal.. can be dealt by another class, no huge loss.<br>
<br>
past 60 there are NO point blank AES.. NO more pillar spells.. and the nukes that we do get, while competitive, are still not good enough to make up for our other weaknesses. since my early 50s ive been COMPLETELY dependent on c3 and mage bracelets as well, with nothing to give in return but TLs, which are pretty useless now with PoP out.<br>
<br>
here's the breakdown.. what classes exist in groups in eq, not by names, but by roles<br>
<br>
tanks - warriors/paladins/shadowknights<br>
healers - druids/clerics/shamans<br>
crowd control - bards/enchanters/FD pullers..<br>
buffing/other group benefits -cleric/druid/beastlord/magician/shaman/shadowknights/bards/enchanters/necromancers/rangers<br>
damage dealers- beastlords/monks/rogues/magicians/necromancers/rangers/wizards<br>
pullers- monks/necros/sks can all FD to single pull, tanks to do other pulling<br>
<br>
everyone other than wizards and rogues have a use other than doing damage within a group setting. rogues arent limited by mana, and have at least SOME defensive skills.<br>
to spell it out for you all, every class which is not a necessary grouping class has abilities that make them desired in a group, a lot of which are unique to that particular class, EXCEPT WIZARDS. ALL non caster groups ive found, being 55+ usually on the planes have 3 NECESSARY roles<br>
tanks, clerics, slowers.<br>
the rest, usually is filled with whatever damage/ puller you can get, at least in my experience.. and wizards are usually the last chosen, not because our DPS sucks or anything, but because thats ALL WE DO. all a wizard does is evac and nuke... escape(and no group wants to have to escape) and damage.<br>
<br>
to put it simply, being a level 60 wizard... i feel i am at a significant disadvantage finding a group simply because of my class... our damage should be better to make up for the fact that we have absolutely nothing else to offer other players in a group setting. the way things are setup, if a wizard makes a mistake and dies (which isn't too difficult in PoP lemme tell ya) it causes a buttload of downtime, need c3 etc.. its as if a healer died. if its a rogue, just rez and go on. mages and necros have pets to protect them.. enchanters can mez. if a wizard gets aggro, he dies. being a wizard isn't easy by a longshot.. concussion tends not to want to cast when you are getting beat for 300+.. and if adds arrive, the mobs don't like you nuking their buddies AT ALL.. and a 20 second root is no solace, either.<br>
<br>
im dependent on c3.. i need to find a bracer when i log on.. with my selfbuffed 1498 hp i can't afford to pull aggro in any group situation.. 60+ solo XP SUCKS ASS it's much better in a group, i am ALWAYS lfg, with 3 or 4 other wizards trolling the planes LFG along with me.<br>
<br>
my proposed solution?? our nukes should be much bigger, not as efficient, and faster casting. 900 mana for 2500 damage in 4 seconds at level 60 sounds more like the wizard i wanted to be.. not this 'little bit better than ice comet' crap.. or 20k plat for sunstrike.. which STILL is just ANOTHER nuke thats a weee bit better! the mobs get 10 times the hp.. the wizards get 1.2 times the nuke. its just not fair.<br>
<br>
i want the ability to do significant damage in a short time back.. wizards don't have that at higher levels.. manaburn is a joke... giant bane is a joke(2dots to do 2k damage is way too expensive).. TLs are a joke.. if i wanted to be efficient, i would have been one of those tree hugging hippie druids. i never wanted to be efficient. i wanted to blow some crap up, not put a chink in ubermob1's hide with my puny wizard ice spear of the solist.. NUKE came from NUCLEAR.. and there's nothing nuclear about casting my biggest nuke and having it do 3%, thats for sure. wow, i blew off a finger. glamorous, isnt it? oo i critted, i got his hand! :-P<br>
<br>
our DPS should be noticably better than normal to make up the fact that we have no other abilities to help out with. the fact is, it's not. our DPS is balanced with other classes.. but we can't buff, and we have no other perks in regards to other classes. no wonder people call us petless mages. they get a 2k nuke at 61.. at 62, we get a 900 something nuke. at 63 we get agnarr's thunder, but by then their pet kicks so much ass it's not even funny.. nor fair.<br>
<br>
i hate having to log on, knowing that somehow along the line i went from nuker.. to glorified rogue/ petless mage. <br>
<br>
so much for blowing stuff up<br>
<br>
-Alatar<br>
