Wizards, like many classes, do have problems getting into groups.  Bottom line is that they we are not a required class; we are an afterthought in most exp groups.  At level 60 at least you have the ability to solo, and solo rather effectively, which is something most classes dont have.<br>
<br>
I have many problems with your judgment of our classes.  We are all about mana efficiency and that is the largest advantage you can bring to a group, sustained damaged.  I was a little disappointed with the fact mages got a bigger, vendor bought nuke at 61.  Actually, I wasnt really satisfied until I worked up my AA crits.  You are really off base with the bane spells; 20pp is a very small price to pay for a 2k irresistible damage spell that is only used on raids anyway.<br>
<br>
My advise would be to stop trolling the planes where you will always be in competition with higher level wizards.  Use concussion early and often, should prevent most aggro concerns you have, especially if the biggest thing you are throwing at the mob is IsoS.  Work on your AA skills, which are truly awesome, and you will regain much of your satisfaction with our class.<br>
<br>
Best Wishes,<br>
