</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bangkirai>bangkirai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/21/03 12:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards are broken..</span><hr size=1> Most wizards, that disagree are the OLD wizards, who are already 60plus now with a good minimum of aa.<br>
<br>
They played a totally different game. For example: They quadded in times, when you would get more xp for the same mobs then nowadays. That means, they could keep staying in xp zones for 3 more levels, then wizards can nowadays.<br>
They were getting groups in Sebilis and other indoors zones, because everyone was in those zones and the people needed a wizard to evac/port out, after xp was done or for emergency. Dead was costly for other classes, so they wanted a wiz to prevent dead.<br>
<br>
All that got changed the last few months. As wizard lvl 50 to 60, you HAVE to do quad kite, but you get way less then the old wizards. So it will cost you more money.(although the ancient wizards didn't had kei, the old ones did).<br>
All the melee/hybrid classes can buy loads of better gear in bazaar to overcome the xp penalty. A wizard not, because the only items u can have to improve yourself are basically the FT items, which are expensive and u can only get a few points in this way.<br>
<br>
People don't want a wizard below lvl 60 in their group, because to be honest, those wizards are a joke with damage dealing. All melee/hybrids have access to such cheap GOOD gear, that they beat easily a wizard in an xp group.<br>
<br>
On the good side: IF you are in a GOOD guild, got ALL your lvl 60 spells, have max. 15FT on items and are 60plus, then yes, you will be a damn good damage dealer. Hehehe, good luck getting all those IF's. <br>
I totally agree wizards are broken and that is mostly the wizards between lvl 1 to 59! They have really crappy spells and no option to improve themself for grouping with items.(extra int/mana items are only usefull for solo, because in a good group, you don't get a break to fill up to max. again)<br>
<br>
Nah wizards need more mana regen. Wizards should have innate crits, that do 2x damage as MINIMUM(like heal spells, insane that those always do double hp). Our aa points in crit should make the spells better then 2x.<br>
<br>
Give us some bigger nukes, put long casting time on it, who cares! We want spells that can kill a mob just before he get enraged. We want to be able to finish a fleeing mob with just 1 nuke, instead of doing 3 a 4 nukes.<br>
Put very short range on bigger nukes, so they can't be used for solo. <br>
<br>
Why can't a wiz even cast an improved invis on someone else or a group? Why don't we have group EB spells?<br>
Why don't we have jinx or luck buffs. So targets rolls higher or lower with every damage roll check?<br>
<br>
Is it soo difficult to come up with some things to improve wizards?<br>
<br>
Bah, why am i writing this anyway, most of these expert wizards really think wizards are totally ok(from their lvl 65plus 30plus aa view) Most of these people hardly played any other online rpg/action game then EQ. I suggest, you play some muds and then you will see how BAD eq is balanced with classes. It's really insane, that loads of muds have more classes/spells/skills more type of mobs options and are still better in balance. It's really insane that these games only have 1 to 5 people in charge? <br>
<br>
Don't forget EQ is just a mud with as extra 3d graphics, too bad it's out of balance really.<br>
<br>
Sometimes i don't think OUR class stinks, nah i think the problem is, that HEALS are too efficient. Our stun line is basically not that usefull other then spell interrupt. I think the main goal of this spellline was also to prevent damage,but why waste soo much mana on a stun, if a complete heal is like 20x as effective?<br>
<br>
Verant made all the heals just easier, so the majority of the people would have a bit more action per hour. Too bad they forgot to increase the other casters to keep the balance.<br>
<br>
