<br>
Maybe I'm an old wizard, but in July 2002, I was still level 55. A month later I was 60th with 23 AA points. Now I'm 65th with something like 55 AA points and FT15 and the works.<br>
<br>
Sure, playing a wizard isn't a walk in the park like some other classes I've played. But to say we're vastly unbalanced against other classes is exaggerating too. All classes have their pros and cons. In the end it all boils down to your social network, you could play cleric (example) and still lack groups and exp and gear, if your social networking skills weren't excellent or if you couldn't play the class. I'm not saying any of posters here can't play wiz, but I'm still wondering why some people say wizards are useless and can't get groups and and and...<br>
<br>
I think wizards are great and that's why my 60+ warrior and cleric are collecting dust. I guess it depends on point of view, some people will never be happy with wizards even if we got &quot;Death Touch&quot; as a skill.<br>
